SIMPLE: leguminous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Leguminous
<hw>Le*gu"mi*nous</hw> <pr>(-m⟦icr⟧*n⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>l⟦eacute⟧gumineux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Pertaining to pulse; consisting of pulse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Belonging to, or resembling, a
very large natural order of plants (<ord>Leguminos⟦ae⟧</ord>), which
bear legumes, including peas, beans, clover, locust trees, acacias, and
mimosas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Leiger</ent>⟦br⟧
